race.comment: BUMP'N'RUN (5) dropped in trip went sent to the provincials for a disappointing eighth over 1600m at Wyong in BM64 class. Earlier runs had merit and scored over 2400m. Has a ton of gear changes and ready to find winning form. HEART OF PLATINUM (11) went back from the outside gate and like the way she attacked the line late when sixth over 2000m at Port Macquarie. Gets a better set-up today and expected to take a hand in the finish. SECRET KEEPER (3) stretches out to this trip for the first time after jumping in class when a battling ninth over 1600m at Newcastle in Highway class. Leading rider booked from the low draw. VENOM WOLF (4) good win two-back, before turning in a slashing performance from near last on the turn when fifth over 2000m at Port Macquarie. Hard to hold out. SEETHING CHUCK (8) had excuses from the sticky gate last start and goes well at this track and trip.
